snippet.textDisplay:
🌸 Inspired from Tagore’s “Anandadhara” 🌸
“পান করে রবি শশী অঞ্জলি ভরিয়া,
সদা দীপ্ত রহে অক্ষয় জ্যোতি,
নিত্য পূর্ণ ধরা জীবনে কিরণে…”

In these lines, I see the reflection of Jesus —
the Akhoy Jyoti, the Eternal Light that never fades. ✨
(John 8:12 — “I am the Light of the world.”)

The sun and moon offer their humble worship,
yet His radiance outshines them all. ☀️🌙
(Revelation 21:23 — “The city does not need the sun or the moon to shine on it, for the glory of God gives it light.”)

Every ray that touches the earth
carries the warmth of His love. 💫
(James 1:17 — “Every good and perfect gift is from above, coming down from the Father of lights.”)

He fills the world with unending brightness —
“Nitya purna dhara jibone kirane” —
for in every breath, His presence overflows.
(John 1:4 — “In Him was life, and that life was the light of all mankind.”)

In Him, life finds its rhythm,
and every day becomes a song of grace. 🎶✝️

Aanondodhara bohichhe bhubone,

Sada deepto rahe akkhayo jyoti—  
Nityo purno dhara jibane kirane.

Swaarthonimagano ki kaarone?  
Chaari dike dekho chaahi hridayo prosari,  
Khudro dukkho sab tuchchho maani;  
Premo bhoriya laho shunyi jibane.
